h3. Summary
User picker "in group" filter does not display all users when having more than 1.000 users on JIRA.


h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Deploy a clean 7.2.6 instance;
# Use the [JIRA Data Generator|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/com.atlassian.jira.plugins.jira-data-generator/server/overview] to create 1.100 random users;
# Manually create 5 users and add them to a test-user group;
# Open the "User Picker", we'll notice that not all users from JIRA are picked as per message _"Displaying users 1 to 20 of 1,000"_ on the screenshot below;
 !1000users-displayed.png|thumbnail! 
# On the "In Group" field, select the "test-user" group and hit the "Filter" button;

h3. Expected Results
* All 5 users added to the test-group to be displayed;
 !group-members.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Actual Results
* Not all users are displayed;
 !user-picker-results.png|thumbnail! 


h3. Workaround
Use the user management view to filter the users from the group instead using the user picker.

